After examining the research published and raising the idea before a discussion group consisting of 100 people, Professor Eastwood and his colleagues defined boredom as the experience of "wanting, but not being able to participate in an activity that fills you".
He claims that the difference between boredom and apathy is that the person does not do anything but wants to do it.
