So we think, why don't we do our best to solve this problem, which is to compose a rap?
1.2 children
The one who doesn't take it so lightly is Singapore's government.
Spending $1.300 a year on policies to encourage citizens to have more children.
A government package for marriages and parents grants up to $15,000 per child, extends maternity leave and shares tax benefits.
But all this has had little effect.
Singapore is a city rich and high-tech state in Southeast Asia, also known for the conservatism of its leaders and strict social controls.
Singapore ' s birth rate, according to its national population division, is currently 1.2 children per woman.
